79: Aggregated means that EDS, CDS, etc resources are all carried by the same gRPC stream.
80: For Envoy's implementation of xDS client logic, there is effectively no difference
81: between aggregated xDS and non-aggregated: they both use the same request/response protos. The
82: non-aggregated case is handled by the aggregated logic, by just
83: happening to only have 1 xDS subscription type to aggregate, i.e., `NewGrpcMuxImpl` only has one
84: `DeltaSubscriptionState` entry in its map.
85: ","endLine":85,"startLine":78},{"content":"85: 
86: However, to the config server, there is a significant difference: when using ADS (i.e. when
87: the user provides an `ads_config` in the bootstrap config), the gRPC client sets
88: its method string to `{Delta,Stream}AggregatedResources`, as opposed to `{Delta,Stream}Clusters`,
89: `{Delta,Stream}Routes`, etc. So, despite using the same request/response protos,
90: and having identical client code, they're actually different gRPC services.
